SQL queries to create the tables used
currently no explanation of the tables, or values within, if you have any questions please e-mail me, wd@drummersdomain.com
may need to add more values into many of these tables, but will take care of that as the situation arises

**************************************************************************************************************************
Main table, contains all tasks and associated values


CREATE TABLE PHPTaskMGR (
  indexID int NOT NULL auto_increment,
  tasklist varchar(50) DEFAULT '' NOT NULL,
  category varchar(50) DEFAULT '' NOT NULL,
  subcategory varchar(50) DEFAULT '' NOT NULL,
  task varchar(50)  DEFAULT '' NOT NULL,
  shortnote varchar(75) DEFAULT '' NOT NULL,
  description text NOT NULL,
  assigned_group varchar(255) DEFAULT 'none' NOT NULL,
  assigned_user varchar(255) DEFAULT 'none' NOT NULL,
  assigned_by varchar(50) DEFAULT '' NOT NULL,
  assigned_date timestamp NOT NULL,
  created_by varchar(50) DEFAULT '' NOT NULL,
  created_date timestamp NOT NULL,
  due_date timestamp NOT NULL,
  private char(1) DEFAULT 'n' NOT NULL,
  hidden char(1) DEFAULT 'n' NOT NULL,
  priority tinyint DEFAULT '5' NOT NULL,
  complete tinyint DEFAULT '0' NOT NULL,
  modified_date timestamp NOT NULL,
  PRIMARY KEY (indexID)
);

**************************************************************************************************************************
User database

CREATE TABLE PHPTaskMGR_user (
indexID int NOT NULL auto_increment,
username varchar(50) NOT NULL,
password varchar(50) NOT NULL,
level int DEFAULT '100' NOT NULL,
realname varchar(50) NOT NULL,
email varchar(50) NOT NULL,
yahoo varchar(50) NOT NULL,
msn varchar(50) NOT NULL,
icq varchar(15) NOT NULL,
aim varchar(50) NOT NULL,
date_added timestamp NOT NULL,
lastIP varchar(15),
last_login timestamp NOT NULL,
PRIMARY KEY(indexID)
);

**************************************************************************************************************************
notes, not used yet, but eventually want the ability for user to post notes about the task probably show below the description on the view task page

CREATE TABLE PHPTaskMGR_notes
indexID int NOT NULL auto_increment,
tasknumer int NOT NULL,
posted_by varchar(50) NOT NULL,
date_posted timestamp NOT NULL,
poster_IP varchar(15) NOT NULL,
notes text NOT NULL,
subject varchar(50) NOT NULL,
PRIMARY KEY(indexID)
);
********************************************************************************************************************************
config table, for now just contains a list of tasklists, Category (and what tasklist they are associated with), Sub cat (and what task list it's associated with)
Doing it this way allows for empty taskilsits/categories/sub cats and not have them display on listing page, other option is to validate at time of display that the list has associated values, this will be quicker I think, allthough it uses a little more space it should be minimal, and more organized
any other tasklist speciffic variables should go here, perhaps tasklist or category, or even sub category specific admins/mods should be added in here as well

CREATE TABLE PHPTaskMGR_config(
indexID int NOT NULL auto_increment,
tasklist varchar(50) DEFAULT 'Main' NOT NULL,
category varchar(50) DEFAULT '-' NOT NULL,
subcategory varchar(50) DEFAULT '-' NOT NULL,
PRIMARY KEY (indexID)
);
